==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Propitiatory
<hw>Pro*pi"ti*a*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>propitiatorius</ets>: cf. F. <ets>propitiatoire</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Having the power to make propitious; pertaining to, or employed in,
propitiation; expiatory; <as>as, a <ex>propitiatory</ex>
sacrifice</as>.</def> <rj><au>Sharp.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Propitiatory</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Propitiatory
<hw>Pro*pi"ti*a*to*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>propitiatorium</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Jewish Antiq.)</fld> <def>The
mercy seat; -- so called because a symbol of the propitiated
Jehovah.</def> <rj><au>Bp. Pearson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Propitious</ent>⟦br⟧
